des:
Listen to this interactive story with a timeless lesson. This is a must have story, the story of Ameera an immigrant in St Paul, who visits an off grid village called Swede Hollow, in St Paul, MN, she finds herself a part of simple folk, living simple lives, but spiritually wealthy with a rich philosophy of life. All along the river Mississippi are scattered such settlements of off grid, low cost dwellings, a rich history of the mid-west.
Read on as you learn to avoid time anomalies, like shifting hours, days and loops.
At any point, you can say "Alexa, stop" to exit the skill. This skill was created using a Skill Blueprint. Your requests to this skill are not shared with the skill developer.
